<subSubSection box="[151,521,186,213]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="81.[151,1437,150,609]" box="[151,521,186,213]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">ORIGINAL DESCRIPTION: 1840b: 25.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="81" pageNumber="82" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="81.[151,1437,150,609]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
<typeStatus box="[151,203,223,249]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">TYPE</typeStatus>
LOCALITY: Rondani gave no 
<typeStatus box="[521,569,223,249]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">type</typeStatus>
locality in his original description but presumably it is 
<taxonomicName authority="" box="[1192,1340,222,249]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Pomacentridae" genus="Parma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="81" pageNumber="82" phylum="Chordata" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Italy">Parma (Italy)</taxonomicName>
because the work deals with Italian species and he wrote “ 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">plures turmatim volitantes in loci udis, tempore presertim vernali, et aliquando in fenestris legi</emphasis>
[I collected many specimens flying in groups, especially in winter, and sometimes on the windows]”.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="81.[151,1437,150,609]" box="[151,584,366,393]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">
<typeStatus box="[151,203,367,393]" pageId="81" pageNumber="82">TYPE</typeStatus>
MATERIAL: not found in this study.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
